OL,3,CHow a family fell foul of travel
OL,4,Cinsurance rules and now face a huge
OL,5,Cbill
OL,7,FAlan's family describes the Greek
OL,8,Fpublic hospital as "scruffy and
OL,9,Funderstaffed". The stark contrast
OL,10,Fbetween the healthcare he desperately
OL,11,Fneeds and what's available has left
OL,12,Fthe family feeling helpless and
OL,13,Fabandoned.
OL,15,FLegally, the only way Alan could fly
OL,16,Fhome to the NHS is on a medical flight
OL,17,Fwith a specialist nurse. That costs
OL,18,F#30,000 and his family can't afford it.
